nl.tudelft.simulation.dsol.experiment

Class ExperimentalFrame<A extends java.lang.Comparable<A>,R extends java.lang.Number & java.lang.Comparable<R>,T extends SimTime<A,R,T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • nl.tudelft.simulation.event.EventProducer
      • nl.tudelft.simulation.dsol.experiment.ExperimentalFrame<A,R,T>
  • Type Parameters:
    A - the absolute storage type for the simulation time, e.g. Calendar, Duration, or Double.
    R - the relative type for time storage, e.g. Long for the Calendar. For most non-calendar types, such as Double or Long, the absolute and relative types are the same.
    T - the simulation time type based on the absolute and relative time.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.util.EventListener, java.util.Iterator<Experiment<A,R,T>>, nl.tudelft.simulation.event.EventListenerInterface, nl.tudelft.simulation.event.EventProducerInterface
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ExperimentalFrame.CalendarDouble, ExperimentalFrame.CalendarFloat, ExperimentalFrame.CalendarLong, ExperimentalFrame.TimeDouble, ExperimentalFrame.TimeDoubleUnit, ExperimentalFrame.TimeFloat, ExperimentalFrame.TimeFloatUnit, ExperimentalFrame.TimeLong

    public class ExperimentalFrame<A extends java.lang.Comparable<A>,R extends java.lang.Number & java.lang.Comparable<R>,T extends SimTime<A,R,T>>
extends nl.tudelft.simulation.event.EventProducer
implements java.util.Iterator<Experiment<A,R,T>>, nl.tudelft.simulation.event.EventListenerInterface
